<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="98" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d98">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/98.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-19">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 19, 1918</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Chinese Government obliged to seek abroad for funds for the Hwai River
                            project. It invites American capital and would probably give an option
                            of one year to Americans to raise loan and make contract for
                            construction. The necessity for the work for the safety and well-fare of
                            millions and its soundness as a business investment undoubted. Mr.
                            Jameson will proceed to the United States with engineering plans to
                            assist in making arrangements for capital if the Red Cross is willing to
                            continue support to the extent of endeavoring to interest American
                            financiers and industrials in the taking up this work. Please
                            instruct.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>